  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Finance Manager",
  "description": "<p>Zagro Group of companies, subsidiaries of a Singapore public limited company, strong in heritage and experienced in providing Agrisolutions to farmers in agriculture and animal husbandry. It manufactures and distributes a wide range of nutrition and protection products for animal health and crop care.</p><p>We are now seeking an energetic, driven, and highly competent professional who is passionate and committed to join our finance team and make a difference to the success and future of our Group.</p><p><strong>FINANCE MANAGER</strong><br /><strong>Base: Singapore</strong></p><p><u>Responsibilities:</u></p><p>•\tManage and oversee the full spectrum of financial operations for the assigned entity, including budgeting, forecasting, taxation and statutory & management reporting.</p><p>•\tEnsure compliance with corporate policies, internal controls, external auditors and all relevant regulatory and statutory requirements.</p><p>•\tCollaborate with cross-functional teams to support business initiatives, operational efficiency, and strategic projects.</p><p>•\tMonitor and manage cash flow, working capital, and capital expenditure to support business sustainability and growth.</p><p>•\tLead and mentor the finance team, fostering a culture of continuous improvement, accountability, and professional development.</p><p>•\tPrepare, analyze, and present financial reports, performance analyses, and key insights to senior management for decision-making.</p><p>•\tUndertake any other ad-hoc duties as assigned to support business and operational needs.</p><p><u>Requirements:</u></p><p>•\tBachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance or ACCA, or a related discipline; CA qualification preferred.</p><p>•\tMinimum 8 years of proven, hands-on experience in finance and accounting, preferably in a trading and/or manufacturing environment with multi-location operations across the Asia Pacific region.</p><p>•\tStrong analytical, problem-solving, and decision-making capabilities.</p><p>•\tExcellent communication and interpersonal skills, with good attitude and the ability to collaborate and influence stakeholders at all levels.</p><p>•\tAudit experience will be an added advantage.</p><p></p>",
